<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1451,2030,2093]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1452,158,905]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,292,2030,2056]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Braun ex Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1864" box="[320,529,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis box="[320,529,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Callitriche deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is native to central South America in an area including southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1259,1330,2030,2056]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1342,1447,2031,2057]" name="Paraguay" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,235,2067,2093]" name="Uruguay" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[397,512,2066,2092]" name="Argentina" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. It is also very widespread as a non-native, with records from 
<collectingCountry box="[1218,1324,2066,2092]" name="Australia" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Australia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1335,1447,2066,2092]" name="Mauritius" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,240,159,185]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[250,348,158,184]" name="Portugal" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[358,502,158,184]" name="South Africa" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[512,597,158,184]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[607,711,158,184]" name="Tanzania" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, and the 
<collectingCountry box="[807,996,158,184]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">United Kingdom</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1009,1204,158,184]" name="Ascension Island" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Ascension Island</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[1225,1411,158,184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="243 - 284" refId="ref15440" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2022) The genus Callitriche (Plantaginaceae, Callitricheae) in Australasia and Oceania. Phytotaxa 547 (3): 243 - 284." type="journal article" year="2022">Lansdown 2022</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[136,237,195,221]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Morocco</collectingCountry>
it was established in the Arboretum of Oued Cherrate for many years and may still persist, it has also been recorded from a garden at Abou-Ali-Al-Youssi, at the former home of Joel Mathez (specimen in RAB). It is not known whether it still persists at either of these sites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,439,302,328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Habitat and ecology:</emphasis>
—In its native range, this species occurs in low-lying, humid areas such as sandy beaches along rivers and dry river beds. Outside its native range it occurs in a wide range of seasonally or permanently moist conditions, such as irrigated areas of nurseries, ornamental beds and greenhouses in botanical gardens, low lying disturbed soil in areas such as un-metalled parking areas and on roadsides (
<bibRefCitation author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[961,1146,410,436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="243 - 284" refId="ref15440" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2022) The genus Callitriche (Plantaginaceae, Callitricheae) in Australasia and Oceania. Phytotaxa 547 (3): 243 - 284." type="journal article" year="2022">Lansdown 2022</bibRefCitation>
).At the Arboretum of Oued Cherrate, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Braun ex Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1864" box="[246,359,446,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis box="[246,359,446,473]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">C. deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grew in shade on the edges of a track leading from a spring that supported 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[1194,1321,446,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis box="[1194,1321,446,473]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">C. cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hammada, S. &amp; Dakki, M. &amp; Ibn Tattou, M. &amp; Ouyahya, A. &amp; Fennane, M." pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="43 - 66" refId="ref15166" refString="Hammada, S., Dakki, M., Ibn Tattou, M., Ouyahya, A. &amp; Fennane, M. (2004) Analyse de la biodiversite floristique des zones humides du Maroc. Flore rare, menacee et halophile. Acta Botanica Malacitana 29: 43 - 66. https: // doi. org / 10.24310 / abm. v 29 i 0.7226" type="journal article" year="2004">
Hammada 
<emphasis box="[136,185,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Fennane, M. &amp; Ibn Tattou, M." box="[269,582,482,509]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="5 - 252" refId="ref14605" refString="Fennane, M. &amp; Ibn Tattou, M. (1998) Catalogue des plantes vasculaires rares, menacees ou endemiques du Maroc. Bocconea 8: 5 - 252." type="journal article" year="1998">Fennane &amp; Ibn Tattou 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,518,544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Braun ex Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1864" box="[370,580,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis box="[370,580,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Callitriche deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[956,1166,518,544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis box="[956,1077,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1343,1447,519,545]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1976" box="[217,346,554,581]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mathezii">
<emphasis box="[217,346,554,581]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">C. mathezii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the small fruit that are blackish when mature. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1976" box="[1245,1373,554,581]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mathezii">
<emphasis box="[1245,1373,554,581]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">C. mathezii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the fruit that are wider than long and at least some on all plants pedunculate, combined with the presence of both 
<specimenCount box="[1356,1377,591,617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[1430,1451,591,617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
flowers in most leaf axils
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
