—Figures in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[492,724,662,689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" refId="ref15552" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2008) Water starworts of Europe. BSBI Handbook No. 11. Botanical Society of the British Isles, London, 180 pp." type="book" year="2008">Lansdown [2008: 25</bibRefCitation>
(16),140, 141]; 
<figureCitation box="[906,995,662,688]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,712,1868]" captionTargetId="figure-280@3.[151,1435,710,1870]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Known distribution of Callitriche spp. in Morocco. A. C. brutia subsp. brutia, with insert map showing the position of Morocco in northwestern Africa. B. C. brutia subsp. naftolskyi. C. C. cribrosa. D. C. lusitanica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875717/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(h) in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Hassemer, G." box="[1067,1446,662,689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="85 - 118" refId="ref15621" refString="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Hassemer, G. (2021) The genus Callitriche (Plantaginaceae: Callitricheae) in South America. Phytotaxa 501 (1): 85 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 501.1.3" type="journal article" year="2021">Lansdown &amp; Hassemer [2021: 88</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 1(h)]).
</paragraph>
